ata  One example he used was the report that 30 to 40 percent of veterans had post traumatic stress disorder   PTSD   leaving out the key words  some symptoms   Having some symptoms is not PTSD   it s normal  Grossman said  explaining that the more realistic number was 8 percent  Although Grossman said the number of veterans with PTSD is lower than the American people are led to believe  he did not discount the need for treatment of the condition  That s why  in fact  the myth of the  macho man or gal   is a problem   We have got to create an environment in which it is OK to get help  he said  He noted that hundreds of thousands of service personnel have been treated for PTSD and have recovered  They re stronger for the experience  he said  Although the subject of Grossman s books is killing  he said the ultimate goal is healing  At the conclusion of his presentation  Grossman posed a question from the novel  Gates of Fire  about the Spartans at Thermopylae   What is the opposite of fear  What quenches fear as water quenches fire  he asked  The answer he offered is  love  He encouraged cadets to go out and use this love   for their fellow soldiers  fellow citizens  nation  and families   as   our nation cries out to our warriors  our protectors     VMI Communications   Marketing News and Features Construction News Institute Report Photos   Videos Cindy Bither Administrative Assistant P   540  464 7207 F   540  464 7443 111 Smith Hall Lexington  VA 24450  Communications   Marketing News and Features Construction News Institute Report Photos   Videos Cindy Bither Administrative Assistant P   540  464 7207 F   540  464 7443 111 Smith Hall Lexington  VA 24450 Communications   Marketing News and Features Construction News Institute Report Photos   Videos Communications   Marketing Communications   Marketing News and Features News and Features Construction News Construction News Institute Report Institute Report Photos   Videos Photos   Videos        Cindy Bither Administ